This paper is primarily focused on the security and privacy aspects of federated learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses the introduction of hidden backdoor functionality into the joint global model, which is a security concern and falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models for predictive tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The examples given in the paper, such as image classification and next-word prediction, are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.SI), respectively.
